result.execSummary:
The defendant Ryan R. Tragoszanos was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Substantial Battery-Intend Bodily Harm [Modifiers: Domestic Abuse - Impairment of Physical Condition, Domestic Abuse Assessments, Repeater], a class I felony, Wisconsin Statutes 940.19(2).

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

supervisions.notes:
Defendant granted credit for 176 days  served and was found eligible for the Substance Abuse Program and Challenge Incarceration Program.
Concurrent with: Sentence in 15CF14 and 15CF22 is to be served concurrent to each other  but consecutive to 15CF23

superMiscConds.notes: Defendant is ordered to pay the DNA surcharge, and to make arrangements to provide a DNA sample for testing through the Clark County Sheriff Department or if on probation, to the Department of Corrections as is required in all felony convictions.
Defendant shall attend counseling, treatments, programming, evaluations as deemed appropriate by the agent releasing all records to the agent upon request

Defendant shall not possess or consume any alcohol, and not go into places that sell alcohol except incidentally such as a grocery store, convenience store or gas station or other such place where alcohol is not sold for consumption on the premises.
  The defendant shall submit to random urine/PBT testing as required by the agent or any law enforcement officer.  
The defendant shall have no contact with J.G. or D.J.  of any kind, whether direct or indirect, including in person, in writing, by phone, by e-mail or other electronic means, through a third party or in any other way.

supervisions.notes:
The defendant shall pay Department of Correction fees as directed by the agent.
Concurrent with: Sentence in 15CF14 and 15CF22 to be served concurrent to each other as are the conditions thereof unless otherwise specified.
